Detailed Description

This is a simple filter intended for client controlled player entities.


The PlayerAvatarFilter behaves almost exactly like the DumbFilter except it does not try and resolve 'on ground' input positions as it assumes it will never be given one.

bool PlayerAvatarFilter::getLastInput ( double &  time,
SpaceID &  spaceID,
EntityID &  vehicleID,
Position3D &  pos,
Vector3 &  posError,
float *  auxFiltered 
) [virtual]

This function gets the last input received by the filter.

Its arguments will be untouched if no input has yet been received.

Parameters:
time Will be set to the time stamp of the last input.
spaceID Will be set to the space ID of the last input.
vehicleID Will be set to the vehicle ID provided in the last input.
pos The position of received in the last input, with its height fully resolved.
posError The amount of uncertainty in the position.
auxFiltered An array of two floats into which the yaw and pitch of the last input will be placed.
Returns:
Returns true if an input existed and the values in the parameters were set.

Implements Filter.

void PlayerAvatarFilter::input ( double  time,
SpaceID  spaceID,
EntityID  vehicleID,
const Position3D &  pos,
const Vector3 &  posError,
float *  auxFiltered 
) [virtual]

This method updates the player filter with a new set of inputs.

Parameters:
time The client time when the input was received.
spaceID The server space that the position resides in.
vehicleID The ID of the vehicle in who's coordinate system the position is defined. A null vehicle ID means that the position is in world coordinates.
pos The new position in either local vehicle or world space/common coordinates.
posError The amount of uncertainty in the position.
auxFiltered If not NULL, a pointer to an array of three floats representing yaw pitch and roll.

Reimplemented from Filter.

void PlayerAvatarFilter::output ( double  time  )  [virtual]

This method updates the owner entity's position and direction with that stored in the filter; but only if time has progressed since the last time the filter was queried.

Parameters:
time The client game time in seconds to which the entity's volatile members should be updated.
